  "schema:version": "1",
  "schema:inLanguage": "en",
  "schema:description": "Abstract: This data set was acquired with a ship-based SeaBeam Classic Multibeam Sonar system during Thomas Washington expedition PASC03WT conducted in 1983 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Harmon Craig). These data files are of MBSystem format and include Swath Bathymetry data and were processed by the GMRT Team using the open source MB-System multibeam sonar processing software as part of the GMRT Synthesis effort. These data are included in the GMRT Synthesis, version 2.0.",
